README: Template/Fedora/
=======================

This directory mirrors the role of `Template/Arch/` but for Fedora-based builds.

- `COMMON/`: lists and overlay content shared by all Fedora flavours.
- `<flavour>/`: per-flavour package lists (examples: `xfce/`, `kde/`).

List files follow the same rules as other templates:
- `*.list` contains one item per line, `#` starts a comment.
- The builder combines `COMMON/` + `<flavour>/` and dedupes.

Fedora uses `dnf` for package management. Package names are the standard
Fedora/RPM names (e.g. `NetworkManager`, `firefox`, `kernel-core`).

Boot: Uses GRUB + grub-mkrescue for hybrid BIOS+UEFI ISO creation.
Initramfs: Uses dracut with the live module (`dracut-live` package).
Live filesystem: Squashfs containing a minimal Fedora root at /squashfs/...
